# Blunno design rules

`app/globals.css` is the source of truth for design tokens.

## Color system

| Token | Hex | Role |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `core-bg` | `#0b0b1a` | Application background |
| `shell` | `#120f25` | Shell, overscroll, theme color |
| `sos` | `#905e8c` | SOS mode |
| `planner` | `#83a9ad` | Planner mode |
| `play` | `#6a3cae` | Play mode |
| `relax` | `#e7b453` | Relax mode |

Derive other UI colors with `color-mix`, rgba, or semantic aliases in `:root` and `@theme inline`. Do not add another accent color without approval.

## Typography

Load fonts only through `next/font/google` in `app/layout.tsx`:

- Plus Jakarta Sans (`--font-plus-jakarta`) for UI and headings
- Tiro Telugu (`--font-tiro-telugu`) for the Blunno wordmark
- Inter (`--font-inter`, `--font-body`) for body and UI text

Do not add fonts or weights without approval because they affect bundle size and LCP.

## Components and interaction

- Reuse primitives from `src/components/ui/`.
- Preserve touch-friendly controls, visible focus states, safe-area padding, and reduced-motion behavior.
- Check mobile layouts at 360, 375, and 393 px widths.
